						<summary>

						<p>Wall of the central shrine of the Narasiṁhasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśivarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1481, Siddhārthi, Chaitra śu. 2,</hi> corresponding to 1559 A.D., March 11, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. It records remission of taxes on the barbers by <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Jillēḷa Veṅgalarājadēva Mahārāju with the sanction of the king and <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Rāmarājadēva-Mahārāju.</p>						

						</summary>
